4.1 Lâefecte de la distÃ ncia en el llenÃ§ament

Volem veure com afecta la distÃ ncia de llenÃ§ament en la precissiÃ³. El primer pas Ã©s calcular la pressisiÃ³ tir per partit, segons la distÃ ncia de llenÃ§ament.

data_sdc <- df %>% group_by(GAME_ID, SHOT_DIST_C, SHOT_RESULT)

df_sdc <- inner_join(data_sdc %>% filter(SHOT_RESULT == "made") %>% 
                       summarise(TR = n()),
                      data_sdc %>% filter(SHOT_RESULT == "missed") %>% 
                       summarise(TF = n()),
                      by = c("GAME_ID","SHOT_DIST_C"), copy = TRUE)

df_sdc <- subset(df_sdc, select = -c(SHOT_RESULT.x, SHOT_RESULT.y))
df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C <- factor(df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C, levels = c("C","M","F"))
df_sdc$TI <- df_sdc$TR + df_sdc$TF
df_sdc$PRES <- 100*df_sdc$TR/df_sdc$TI

ComprovaciÃ³ normalitat.

Ens volem centrar en comparar baixada de pressisiÃ³ amb lâaugment de la distÃ ncia. Primer comprovarem si cada atribut segueix una distribuciÃ³ normal. Els Q-Q Plots indiquen que podem tenir aquestes distribucions normals.

par(mfrow=c(1,3))
qqnorm(df_sdc$PRES[df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C == "C"], main = "CLOSE")
qqline(df_sdc$PRES[df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C == "C"])

qqnorm(df_sdc$PRES[df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C == "M"], main = "MEDIUM")
qqline(df_sdc$PRES[df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C == "M"])

qqnorm(df_sdc$PRES[df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C == "F"], main = "FAR")
qqline(df_sdc$PRES[df_sdc$SHOT_DIST_C == "F"])

Amb els Q-Q Plots estem molt convenÃ§uts de la normalitat del nostre conjunt de dades, perÃ² per si acas realitzarem una comprovaciÃ³ mitjanssant el Test de Kolmogorov-Smirnov.

df$CLUTCH_C <- relevel(df$CLUTCH, ref = "0")
df$ATTACK_TYPE_C <- relevel(df$ATTACK_TYPE, ref = "Long")
model <- glm(SHOT_RESULT ~ SHOT_DIST + CLUTCH_C + ATTACK_TYPE_C + CLOSE_DEF_DIST,
            data = df,
            family = "binomial")

Fem prediccions

df$SHOT_RESULT_pred <- predict.glm(model, df, type = "response")
summary(model)
